The paper discusses citation analysis, which is commonly used in the field of computer science to evaluate the impact of research publications. The paper also mentions the use of percentile rank classes, which is a common approach in information retrieval (IR) research. Therefore, cs.DL (Digital Libraries) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also discusses the normalization of papers, which is relevant to the sub-category of cs.CY (Computational Geometry) as well as cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Finally, the paper mentions the potential negative correlation between citation indicators, which is relevant to the sub-category of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
